 <i>bald</i> ‘bold, brave’. The first element was altered under the influence of Greek <i>theos</i> ‘god’. This name was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":6,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Theobald De Verdun II was born on 8 September 1448, in Cheadle, Staffordshire, England. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Elizabeth De Clare. He died on 27 July 1489, in Alton, Staffordshire, England, at the age of 40."},"et":{"8 September 1448–27 July 1489":"8. september 1448–27. juuli 1489","1450–1506":"1450–1506","1470–1500":"1470–1500","1470–1712":"1470–1712","1448–1489":"1448–1489","1448":"1448","1712":"1712","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","after 1470":"pärast 1470","27 July 1489":"27. juuli 1489","1450":"1450","1470":"1470","1506":"1506","8 September 1448":"8. september 1448","Alton, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Alton, Staffordshire, England","Cheadle, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheadle, Staffordshire, England","Middlesex, England":"Middlesex, England"},"fi":{"8 September 1448–27 July 1489":"8. syyskuuta 1448–27. heinäkuuta 1489","1450–1506":"1450–1506","1470–1500":"1470–1500","1470–1712":"1470–1712","1448–1489":"1448–1489","1448":"1448","1712":"1712","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1455":"1455","after 1470":"1470 jälkeen","27 July 1489":"27. heinäkuuta 1489","1450":"1450","1470":"1470","1506":"1506","8 September 1448":"8. syyskuuta 1448","Alton, Staffordshire, England, Unite